TITLE: Returning Relations Count with Select in Prisma Client
DESCRIPTION: This query uses select instead of include to return only the post count for each user without including any other fields. This is useful when you only need the count information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/056-aggregation-grouping-summarizing.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const usersWithCount = await prisma.user.findMany({
  select: {
    _count: {
      select: { posts: true },
    },
  },
})
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
  _count: {
    posts: 3
  }
}
```

