TITLE: Creating Multiple User Records with Prisma Client in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create multiple user records in a single query using the Prisma Client createMany() method. It also demonstrates the use of skipDuplicates option to handle duplicate unique keys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/030-crud.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const createMany = await prisma.user.createMany({
  data: [
    { name: 'Bob', email: 'bob@prisma.io' },
    { name: 'Bobo', email: 'bob@prisma.io' }, // Duplicate unique key!
    { name: 'Yewande', email: 'yewande@prisma.io' },
    { name: 'Angelique', email: 'angelique@prisma.io' },
  ],
  skipDuplicates: true, // Skip 'Bobo'
})
```

