TITLE: Defining Prisma Schema and Models - Prisma
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure of the database using Prisma's schema language. It includes the client generator configuration, the database connection setup using an environment variable, and the definition of the `User` and `Post` models with their fields, types, directives (like `@id`, `@unique`, `@default`, `@relation`), and the one-to-many relationship between them.
