TITLE: Batching GraphQL Queries with Prisma Client's Fluent API
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use findUnique() with the fluent API to leverage Prisma's dataloader for batching queries. This approach optimizes multiple individual user.posts queries into batched database requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/100-query-optimization-performance.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const User = objectType({
  name: 'User',
  definition(t) {
    t.nonNull.int('id')
    t.string('name')
    t.nonNull.string('email')
    t.nonNull.list.nonNull.field('posts', {
      type: 'Post',
      resolve: (parent, _, context) => {
        return context.prisma.user
          .findUnique({
            where: { id: parent.id || undefined },
          })
          .posts()
      },
    })
  },
})
```

