TITLE: Modifying a Specific Operation Across All Models
DESCRIPTION: Creates an extension that applies a limit of 100 results to all findMany operations across all models in the schema by setting the take parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/300-client-extensions/120-query.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const prisma = new PrismaClient().$extends({
  query: {
    $allModels: {
      async findMany({ model, operation, args, query }) {
        // set `take` and fill with the rest of `args`
        args = { ...args, take: 100 }

        return query(args)
      },
    },
  },
})
```

