TITLE: Continuing Cursor-based Pagination with Prisma Client in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to continue cursor-based pagination. It returns 4 Post records after the supplied cursor, skipping the cursor itself.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/055-pagination.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const secondQueryResults = await prisma.post.findMany({
  take: 4,
  skip: 1, // Skip the cursor
  cursor: {
    id: myCursor,
  },
  where: {
    title: {
      contains: 'Prisma' /* Optional filter */,
    },
  },
  orderBy: {
    id: 'asc',
  },
})

const lastPostInResults = secondQueryResults[3] // Remember: zero-based index! :)
const myCursor = lastPostInResults.id // Example: 52
```

