TITLE: Handling Transaction Retries with Serializable Isolation
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to handle transaction retries with Serializable isolation level to avoid write conflicts and deadlocks. Implements a retry mechanism for P2034 errors with a maximum retry limit.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/058-transactions.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Prisma, PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client'

const prisma = new PrismaClient()
async function main() {
  const MAX_RETRIES = 5
  let retries = 0

  let result
  while (retries < MAX_RETRIES) {
    try {
      result = await prisma.$transaction(
        [
          prisma.user.deleteMany({
            where: {
              /** args */
            },
          }),
          prisma.post.createMany({
            data: {
              /** args */
            },
          }),
        ],
        {
          isolationLevel: Prisma.TransactionIsolationLevel.Serializable,
        }
      )
      break
    } catch (error) {
      if (error.code === 'P2034') {
        retries++
        continue
      }
      throw error
    }
  }
}
```

