TITLE: Configuring Datadog Tracer with Prisma Instrumentation
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript code that initializes the Datadog tracer and configures Prisma instrumentation. It sets up the tracer provider and registers the Prisma instrumentation to capture spans for all database queries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/800-guides/190-data-dog.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import Tracer from "dd-trace";
import {
  PrismaInstrumentation,
  registerInstrumentations,
} from "@prisma/instrumentation";

const tracer = Tracer.init({
  apmTracingEnabled: true,
  service: "prisma-datadog-tracing",
  version: "1.0.0",
  profiling: true
});

const provider = new tracer.TracerProvider();

// Register the provider globally
provider.register();

registerInstrumentations({
  instrumentations: [
    new PrismaInstrumentation({
      enabled: true,
    }),
  ],
  tracerProvider: provider,
});

export { tracer };
```

