TITLE: Define Dockerfile using node:slim (Dockerfile)
DESCRIPTION: Dockerfile configuration using the Debian-based `node:slim` image. It installs `openssl`, sets the working directory, copies package files and application code, installs dependencies using `npm ci`, and defines the command to run migrations, generate Prisma Client, and start the server.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/800-guides/130-docker.mdx#_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: dockerfile
CODE:
```
FROM node:slim

RUN apt-get update -y \
&& apt-get install -y openssl

WORKDIR /usr/src/app

COPY package.json package-lock.json ./

COPY . .

RUN npm ci

CMD ["sh", "-c", "npm run db:deploy && npm run dev"]
```

