TITLE: Idempotent Stripe Customer Creation Flow
DESCRIPTION: Improved implementation that adds idempotency by checking for existing customers before creation and handling both create and update scenarios safely.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/058-transactions.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const numTeammates = await prisma.user.count({
  where: {
    teams: {
      some: {
        id: teamId,
      },
    },
  },
})

// Find customer in Stripe
let customer = await stripe.customers.get({ externalId: teamID })

if (customer) {
  // If team already exists, update
  customer = await stripe.customers.update({
    externalId: teamId,
    plan: 'plan_id',
    quantity: numTeammates,
  })
} else {
  customer = await stripe.customers.create({
    // If team does not exist, create customer
    externalId: teamId,
    plan: 'plan_id',
    quantity: numTeammates,
  })
}

// Update the team with the customer id to indicate that they are a customer
// and support querying this customer in Stripe from our application code.
await prisma.team.update({
  data: {
    customerId: customer.id,
  },
  where: {
    id: teamId,
  },
})
```

