TITLE: Defining UserUniqueInput and User Query in Nexus
DESCRIPTION: Code-first schema definition with Nexus, creating both an input type for unique user lookups and a user query field that accepts this input type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/800-more/300-upgrade-guides/800-upgrade-from-prisma-1/05-upgrading-prisma-binding-to-nexus.mdx#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { inputObjectType, arg } from '@nexus/schema'

const UserUniqueInput = inputObjectType({
  name: 'UserUniqueInput',
  definition(t) {
    t.string('id')
    t.string('email')
  },
})

const Query = queryType({
  definition(t) {
    // ... previous queries

    t.field('user', {
      type: 'User',
      args: {
        userUniqueInput: arg({
          type: 'UserUniqueInput',
          nullable: false,
        }),
      },
    })
  },
})
```

