TITLE: Creating a Draft Post with Prisma 1
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a draft post using Prisma 1's `createPost` method.  It defines a GraphQL mutation field named `createDraft` that accepts `title`, `content`, and `authorId` as arguments.  The `resolve` function uses the Prisma context to create the post and connect it to the author.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/800-more/300-upgrade-guides/800-upgrade-from-prisma-1/04-upgrading-nexus-prisma-to-nexus.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
mutationType({
  definition(t) {
    t.field('createDraft', {
      type: 'Post',
      args: {
        title: stringArg({ nullable: false }),
        content: stringArg(),
        authorId: stringArg({ nullable: false }),
      },
      resolve: (_, args, context) => {
        return context.prisma.createPost({
          title: args.title,
          content: args.content,
          author: {
            connect: { id: args.authorId },
          },
        })
      },
    })
  },
})
```

