TITLE: Raw Queries in Prisma Transaction for MongoDB
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use raw MongoDB queries within a Prisma $transaction, including find, aggregate, and runCommand operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/100-queries/058-transactions.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const [findRawData, aggregateRawData, commandRawData] =
  await prisma.$transaction([
    prisma.user.findRaw({
      filter: { age: { $gt: 25 } },
    }),
    prisma.user.aggregateRaw({
      pipeline: [
        { $match: { status: 'registered' } },
        { $group: { _id: '$country', total: { $sum: 1 } } },
      ],
    }),
    prisma.$runCommandRaw({
      aggregate: 'User',
      pipeline: [
        { $match: { name: 'Bob' } },
        { $project: { email: true, _id: false } },
      ],
      explain: false,
    }),
  ])
```

