TITLE: Prisma ORM Schema: Inline 1-1 Introspection as 1-n
DESCRIPTION: This Prisma schema shows the result of introspecting a database with an inline 1-1 relation where no `UNIQUE` constraint was defined on the foreign key column. The `Profile` field in the `User` model now is a `Profile[]`, which indicates a one-to-many relationship instead of a one-to-one relationship.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/800-more/300-upgrade-guides/800-upgrade-from-prisma-1/02-schema-incompatibilities-mysql.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: prisma
CODE:
```
```prisma file=schema.prisma showLineNumbers
model User {
  id      String    @id
  Profile Profile[]
}

model Profile {
  id   String  @id
  user String?
  User User?   @relation(fields: [user], references: [id])
}
```
```

