TITLE: Auto-Syncing Data Using Prisma Client Extension with libSQL
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to implement automatic synchronization after create, update, or delete operations using a Prisma Client extension. It extends the PrismaClient to call libsql.sync() after any write operation, ensuring the embedded replica stays in sync with the remote database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/050-overview/500-databases/900-turso.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const prisma = new PrismaClient().$extends({
  query: {
    $allModels: {
      async $allOperations({ operation, model, args, query }) {
        const result = await query(args)

        // Synchronize the embedded replica after any write operation
        if (['create', 'update', 'delete'].includes(operation)) {
          await libsql.sync()
        }

        return result
      }
    }
  }
})
```

