TITLE: Solution 3: Setting onUpdate to NoAction in author Relation
DESCRIPTION: Third solution that breaks the cascade chain by modifying the author relation in the Post model to use NoAction for the onUpdate referential action, preventing the cascade from propagating through to Comment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/100-prisma-schema/20-data-model/20-relations/410-referential-actions/100-special-rules-for-referential-actions.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: prisma
CODE:
```
model Post {
  id       Int       @id @default(autoincrement())
  authorId Int
  //delete-next-line
  author   User      @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id])
  //add-next-line
  author   User      @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id], onUpdate: NoAction)
  comments Comment[]
}
```

