TITLE: Implementing beforeExit Hook in Prisma Client with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the beforeExit hook in Prisma Client. This hook allows you to run code before Prisma Client disconnects, which is useful for graceful shutdown scenarios in long-running applications.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/000-setup-and-configuration/050-databases-connections/100-connection-management.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const prisma = new PrismaClient()

prisma.$on('beforeExit', async () => {
  console.log('beforeExit hook')
  // PrismaClient still available
  await prisma.message.create({
    data: {
      message: 'Shutting down server',
    },
  })
})
```

