TITLE: Handling Prisma Unique Constraint Errors in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of error handling in TypeScript when attempting to create a user with a duplicate email, demonstrating how to catch and handle Prisma's unique constraint violation errors using instanceof checks
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/200-prisma-client/700-debugging-and-troubleshooting/230-handling-exceptions-and-errors.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { PrismaClient, Prisma } from '@prisma/client'

const client = new PrismaClient()

try {
  await client.user.create({ data: { email: 'alreadyexisting@mail.com' } })
} catch (e) {
  if (e instanceof Prisma.PrismaClientKnownRequestError) {
    // The .code property can be accessed in a type-safe manner
    if (e.code === 'P2002') {
      console.log(
        'There is a unique constraint violation, a new user cannot be created with this email'
      )
    }
  }
  throw e
}
```

