TITLE: Automatic Transactions with Sequelize
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use automatic transaction management in Sequelize with try/catch for handling errors. This approach uses an explicit rollback in the catch block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/200-orm/800-more/400-comparisons/02-prisma-and-sequelize.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
return sequelize.$transaction(async (transaction) => {
  try {
    const user = await User.create({
      name: 'Alice',
      email: 'alice@prisma,io',
    })
    const post1 = await Post.create({
      title: 'Join us for GraphQL Conf in 2019',
    })
    const post2 = await Post.create({
      title: 'Subscribe to GraphQL Weekly for GraphQL news',
    })
    await user.setPosts([post1, post2])
  } catch (e) {
    return transaction.rollback()
  }
})
```

