TITLE: Required MDX Frontmatter for Prisma Guides
DESCRIPTION: Example of the mandatory frontmatter structure for a Prisma ORM guide using MDX. Includes fields like title, metaTitle, description, sidebar_label, and image, with explanations for each field's purpose and formatting requirements (sentence case).
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/content/800-guides/999-making-guides.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: mdx
CODE:
```
---
title: 'How to [do something] with Prisma ORM'
metaTitle: 'How to [do something] with Prisma ORM'
description: 'Learn how to [do something] with Prisma ORM'
sidebar_label: '[Concise Label]'
image: '/img/guides/[guide-name]-cover.png'
community_section: true
---
```

