TITLE: Using mdtool to Insert Documentation Files
DESCRIPTION: Example of using mdtool to insert a new file at a specific position in the documentation hierarchy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/prisma/docs/blob/main/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
$ mdtool insert INDEX

# e.g.:
$ mdtool insert 2

# Result: for files 01-a, 02-b, 03-c, and 04-d; 03-c is renamed to 04-c and 04-d is renamed to 05-d so you can create a new file at index 2
```

